  <div id="content">
      <h2>Curlpaste</h2>
      <p>
        Curlpaste is a utility to post text files to a number of pastebin sites using curl and Lua.
        </p>
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <li>Support for several different pastebins.</li>
        Available services are <a href="http://codepad.org">codepad (default)</a>, <a href="http://pasteit.ghost1227.com">ghost</a>,
        <a href="http://pastebin.ca">ca</a>, <a href="http://paste.plurk.com">lodgeit</a>, <a href="http://dpaste.com">dpaste</a>, and
        <a href="http://fpaste.org">fpaste</a>
        <li>Multiple file uploading in one command, by default a separate link for each but you may specify that curlpaste should concat them into one paste.</li>
        <li>Pasting from the X primary selection buffer as well as putting the returned url on the clipboard</li>
        <li>Specify description, nick, expiration date, language, service, or let curlpaste use the sensible default options.</li>
        <li>Many more! See <a href="help.txt">help.txt</a> for a full list.</li>
	</div>
